Description: Two joining sherds of handle and shoulder of East Greek pottery amphora or oenochoe; cream slip; traces of reddish glaze; fresh break.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), Well 101 (= Well 5)
Curator's comments: Marked '101' in pencil. Possibly from same vessel as 1965,0930.743
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.022)
